org.openscience.cdk.qsar.model.R
Class LinearRegressionModelSummary

java.lang.Object
  org.openscience.cdk.qsar.model.R.LinearRegressionModelSummary
Deprecated. 

public class LinearRegressionModelSummary
extends java.lang.Object

A class that represents a summary of a linear regression model. This class essentially wraps the result of summar.lm. As with other backend classes this class should not be instantiated directly by the user, though the various fields may be accessed with the provided methods.

Author:
Rajarshi Guha
Requires:
r-project
Belongs to CDK module:
qsar

Constructor for an object that wraps the return value from summary.lm. This should not be instantiated directly. The class is meant to be instantiated from an R session

Parameters:
residuals - An array of residuals
coeff - An array of coeffs and associated statistics
coeffColNames - The names of the columns for the coefficient matrix
coeffRowNames - The names of the rows for the coefficient matrix
sigma - The residual error
df - The degrees of freedom
rsq - The R^2 value
adjrsq - The adjusted R^2 value
fstat - The value of the F-statistic

getCoeff

public double[][] getCoeff()
Deprecated. 
Returns the coefficients and associated statistics. This method will return the coefficients as well as the standard error in the coefficients, t-values and p-values corresponding to the t-values. Thus the return value is a 2D array of doubles, with rows equal to the number of coefficients (ie 1+num predictor variables) and 4 columns containing the estimated coefficients and the above statistics, in the order mentioned above.

Returns:
A 2-D array of doubles containing the estimated coefficients and associated statistics
